{
  "texts": [
    "The RetinaNet models trained on CathAI's dataset were deployed to analyze every frame of each video in our dataset, which includes videos of both the LCA and RCA.",
    "When a video was classified as pertaining to the RCA, as determined by Algorithm 1, the RetinaNet models were programmed to exclude predictions for LCA segments, and the inverse is true for LCAidentified videos.",
    "5 The RetinaNet models were applied to all frames of our LCA and RCA videos, as identified by Algorithm 1.",
    "To streamline this process, specific elements were established to facilitate efficient and accurate processing:",
    "• Reference frame: Frame within a video where there is a stenosis box identified."
  ]
}